      "text": "Market Notice Details\n\nTo: Notice_Operations@lists.ercot.com,Notice_PRR_SCR@lists.ercot.com,Notice_Settlements@lists.ercot.com\n\nSent: 5/26/23, 2:52 PM\n\nSubject: M-D050523-02 Implementation Details for ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service\n\n---\n\nNOTICE DATE: May 26, 2023\n\nNOTICE TYPE: M-D050523-02 Operations\n\nSHORT DESCRIPTION: Implementation Details for ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service\n\nINTENDED AUDIENCE: All Market Participants\n\nDAYS AFFECTED: June 9, 2023\n\nLONG DESCRIPTION: On June 9, 2023, ERCOT will implement changes related to the ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service (ECRS). The implementation of ECRS will complete work being done to implement Nodal Protocol Revision Request (NPRR) 863, Creation of ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service and Revisions to Responsive Reserve, and related Revision Requests. Specifically, the following Nodal Protocol Revisions Requests (NPRRs), Nodal Operating Guide Revision Requests (NOGRRs) and Other Binding Document Revision Requests (OBDRRs) will be implemented as a part of this effort.\n\nOn June 9, 2023, language associated with the following Revision Requests will be implemented.\n\n- NPRR992, Updated Day-Ahead Liability for NPRR863, Creation of ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service and Revisions to Responsive Reserve\n- NPRR903, Day-Ahead Market Timing Deviations\n- NPRR863, Creation of ERCOT Contingency Reserve Services and Revisions to Responsive Reserve\n\nNPRR1096, Require Sustained Two-Hour Capability for ECRS and Four-Hour Capability for Non-Spin\n\nNOGRR187, Related to NPRR863, Creation of ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service and Revisions to Responsive Reserve\n\n- ODBRR044, Related to NPRR1085, Ensuring Continuous Validity of Physical Responsive Capability (PRC) and Dispatch through Timely Changes to Resource Telemetry and Current Operating Plans (COPs)\n- OBDRR043, Related to NPRR1148, Language Cleanup Related to ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service (ECRS)\n- NOGRR186, Alignment Changes for March 1, 2019 Nodal Operating Guide – NPRR863\n- NPRR1148, Language Cleanup Related to ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service (ECRS)\n- NPRR1085, Ensuring Continuous Validity of Physical Responsive Capability (PRC) and Dispatch through Timely Changes to Resource Telemetry and Current Operating Plans (COPs)\n- NPRR1015, Clarification of DAM implementation of NPRR863 Phase 2\n\nERCOT hosted a workshop on April 3, 2023 to outline the implementation details related to ECRS. Market Operations Test Environment (MOTE) testing in support of this implementation is currently in progress and weekly Market Readiness meetings are currently taking place every Tuesday at 10:00 am through to June 6, 2023. The link to the next Weekly Market Readiness meeting is located here.\n\nACTION REQUIRED: QSEs that manage Resources are encouraged to participate in weekly ECRS Market Readiness calls and MOTE submission activities from April 20 - June 6, 2023. A QSE that wishes to qualify Resources to provide ECRS may submit a request for qualification by contacting its respective ERCOT Account Manager.\n\nADDITIONAL INFORMATION: Pursuant to Nodal Protocol Section 21.6, Nodal Protocol Revision Implementation, and Nodal Operating Guide Section 1.3.5, Nodal Operating Guide Revision Implementation, ERCOT is required to provide notice as soon as practicable, but no later than ten days prior to implementation.\n\nCONTACT: If you have any questions, please contact your ERCOT Account Manager. You may also call the general ERCOT Client Services phone number at (512) 248-3900 or contact ERCOT Client Services via email at ClientServices@ercot.com.\n\nIf you are receiving email from a public ERCOT distribution list that you no longer wish to receive, please follow this link in order to unsubscribe from this list: http://lists.ercot.com.\n\nmm",
